libesmtp
------------------------------------------
libESMTP is an SMTP client which manages posting (or submission of) 
electronic mail via a preconfigured Mail Transport Agent (MTA). It may 
be used as part of a Mail User Agent (MUA) or other program that must be 
able to post electronic mail but where mail functionality is not that 
program's primary purpose.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  openssl-0.9.8e-3
  exim OR ssmtp OR another SMTP server

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  bison-2.3-1
  cygport-0.2.11-1
  flex-2.5.33-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.stafford.uklinux.net/libesmtp/

Canonical download:
  http://www.stafford.uklinux.net/libesmtp/download.html

License:
  LGPL-2.1

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libesmtp-1.0.4-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libesmtp-1.0.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libesmtp-1.0.4-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libesmtp-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libesmtp-devel-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libesmtp5-1.0.4-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

